          "meaning": "The body reacts before the mind catches up. The anterior insula \u2014 the cortex's interoceptive hub, mapping body-state signals into felt sensation \u2014 fires high while the dorsolateral prefrontal cortex stays quiet. This pattern is the cortical signature of a moment that arrives in the chest before the brain has decided whether to care. Pre-reflective. Bypasses analysis.",
